Hydroclimate: Infilling of the lagoon, associated with wet event/ low sea levels, but not as low as during LGM/ shift of ITCZ
Vegetation and fire: Low fire activity and limited availability of biomass to burn. Mostly aquatic plants, with limited contributions of C3 (sedges) and C4 (grasses) species

Hydroclimate: Small, shallow lagoon reflecting dry and cool conditions
Vegetation and fire: Increased C3 vegetation and low fire activity.
Low fire activity continues.  Mixture of land and aquatic plants, with dominance of sedges.

Hydroclimate: Expansion and deepening of the lagoon/sea level high stand and higher precipitation
Vegetation and fire: Dominance of terrestrial plant input (C3, sedges and arboreal) and peaks in fire activity between 9.3 ka and 7.1 ka. More availability of biomass to burn (C3)

Hydroclimate: Present stabilization and deepening of the lagoon
Vegetation and fire: Return to a mixture of aquatic and land derived plants, mostly sedges (C4)
